#CircuitBreakerSG D-52

My mama ordered 3 big slabs of Pork Belly for me to make the family's favourite Roast Pork Belly (Siew Yoke). Crispy skin & flavorful meat. I'm so glad the family loves it.

The biggest difficulty is chopping the roast pork which I'm really bad at it, any tips?

The other dishes are Napa Cabbage with Oyster Mushroom, Picked Cucumber & Onion Omelette.

Happy #dinner all 🤗

Wa sio bak heaven there, you are amazing my dear!!!! 👍👏👏😍
No need to chop, I can take the whole thing! 😉
@bionickitty01 Thanks so much for sharing 🤗 Going to try that soon 👍
I've seen people score the meat before cooking. That way, when you cut along the scored sections you will get these clean and neat pieces
@yvonnemsw lol no. Thank you for the cravings. I just ordered some today 😜
Makes me so hungry now. I always like to add some fried garlic to the roast pork belly to give an extra crisp. Also garlic help lower cholesterol level.
Cut against the skin, or cut from the meat section first.
@sgkitchennoob Love it so much, will probably have it again this week 😆
@yvonnemsw oh my! got to do a video and record the crackling sound when you cut it ! It’s so addictive to listen to HAHA!
@sgkitchennoob I'll try, I'm a noob doing vid 😆
Omg ! That skin in the video! 💥💥💥
